name: showScreenSet
description: Shows a Gigya screen set. Either locally hosted or hosted in the Gigya console.

params.name: opts.screenSet
params.description: Screen set to use. Defaults to {@link GigyaWrapper#screenSet}

params.name: opts.containerID
params.description: DOM id of screen set container. Defaults to {@link GigyaWrapper#containerID}

params.name: opts.customLang
params.description: An object which overrules the error message for the selected language.

params.name: opts.onBeforeScreenLoad
params.description: This function is fired on before screen load.

name: hideScreenSet
description: Hides a Gigya screen set. Either locally hosted or hosted in the Gigya console.

params.name: opts.screenSet
params.description: Screen set to use. Defaults to {@link GigyaWrapper#screenSet}

params.name: opts.containerID
params.description: DOM id of screen set container. Defaults to {@link GigyaWrapper#containerID}

name: registerEventListeners
description: register to global Gigya events like user login or logout.

params.name: eventListeners
params.description: an object of functions that are fired upon global gigya events.

name: getAccountInfo
description: Hides a Gigya screen set. Either locally hosted or hosted in the Gigya console.

params.name: include
params.description: A comma-separated list of fields to include in the response. The possible values are: identities-active, identities-all, loginIDs, emails, profile, data, regSource, and irank.

return.description: Resolves an object with errorCode, errorMessage and user account info based on the include parameter.
